(43173, 1456, 42331, 'MIdreesTaj', 867, '', 1250179028, '[quote=KageFox]What about a target pistol in either of these calibers? Cause, if I''m not mistaken, the 7.62mm has ballistics pretty close to the .38 Super, which is an oft-used caliber in target competitions in US.[/quote]\n\n7.62 or 30cal usually holds higher BCs.. ballistics wise, 30 caliber is probably the most venerable caliber in all calibers. \n.38 is ballistic wise closer or equal to .357 or closer to 9mm not 7.62. \n30cal is more of a rifle round where higher ballistics provide usefulness. \ncalibers larger as 9mm are still good for long range pistol shooting.. 9mm is even a preferred round for long range shots on steel targets in competitions.', 0, 1, '119.152.26.163', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 1962, 49693),
