(45542, 1505, 43901, 'Skeeter60', 861, '', 1250884583, 'The death of the major without firing a shot is a clear evidence of what I have been harping, if you are not familiar with your weapon and have not trained regularly don''t pull out your weapon and if you do pull out your weapon use it to its best potential.\nI will annalyse this particular case for you;\n\nMajor retired about 17 years ago\nHis revolver was .38 S&W ( please do  not mix with .38 special )\n\nHe had never fired it presumably as the bullets for this caliber are not available for the last 35 years\n\nHe may be having bullets from the first world war which never fired\n\nHis reluctance to shoot a revolver he had not fired in the last three decades led to this trajedy\n\nHad he been a gun person he would be carrying at least a .38special and instead of trying to scare the bad guys by showing his gun would have shot the two jokers in seconds', 0, 1, '119.154.49.100', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2016, 52178),
