(49187, 1668, 49135, '12GAUGE', 608, '', 1251839238, 'yes there are more gauges in shotgun such as: (in descending order)\n\n1. 4 gauge\n2. 8 gauge\n3. 10 gauge\n4. 12 gauge\n5. 16 gauge\n6. 20 gauge\n7. 0.410 bore (this is the true bore size in inches, but this is how u mostly hear about it)\n\nand this 25% extra shots for a shotgun is totally unheard of, may be i''m unable to understand what u are saying. but if u''r talking about chamber length then:\n\nchamber length is the length of the cartridge that can be inserted in a shotgun''s chamber. commonly used chamber lengths are:\n\n1. 2.75 inch (standard, most commonly found)\n2. 3 inch (pretty much standard now, not easily found in Pakistan however)\n4. 3.5 inch (very hot, brutal recoil and not much benefit)\n\na cartridge for a shorter chamber can be easily/safely fired in a longer chamber however must not, i''ll repeat must not fire a cartridge in shorter chamber that has been designed for a longer chamber.\n\nRegards.', 0, 1, '58.65.151.249', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2222, 56052),
