(50488, 1710, 50265, 'MHMalik', 801, '', 1252209418, 'Well NATO and POF 9mm is loaded much hotter than normal rounds.\n\nI would not be very comfortable using them in firearms not rated for +P+.\n\nHaving said that, most good quality handguns are rated for +P at least and are tested to +25% higher pressures, so they should be fine. If your handgun is not rated for AT LEAST +P you shouldnt use military rounds in 9mm. IN any case these are harder on the springs and slides and decrease the life of the weapon with extensive usage.', 0, 1, '202.69.15.12', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2273, 57478),
