(50685, 1710, 50265, 'Ilyas', 455, '', 1252253346, '[quote=MHMalik]Well NATO and POF 9mm is loaded much hotter than normal rounds.\n\nI would not be very comfortable using them in firearms not rated for +P+.\n\nHaving said that, most good quality handguns are rated for +P at least and are tested to +25% higher pressures, so they should be fine. If your handgun is not rated for AT LEAST +P you shouldnt use military rounds in 9mm. IN any case these are harder on the springs and slides and decrease the life of the weapon with extensive usage.[/quote]\n\nWell will someone please tell the members, which of the commonly available handguns like PT92, Pt99, 24/7, CF98, NP34, \nStoeger Cougar 8000, Zastava CZ999, Sarsilmaz, Beretta 92FS, Glocks etc,  are rated +P+ or +P? It would help all the members to be more careful while buying ammo.', 0, 1, '116.58.96.5', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2273, 57685),
