(51723, 1, 1, 'RWS shooter', 1136, '', 1252533357, '[quote=KageFox][quote=RWS shooter]NOOOO\n\nI did not come here to teach but to learn from YOU\n\nI have many air rifles and plenty off dfifferent brands pellets, you name the brand and I have it!!\n\nat 40 yards\n\nwould you  consider the RWS 48 or the TX 200 and with what pellets maybe the  RWS 460 or the HW97\n\nlot''s of air rifles and opinion''s but strill a valid question\n\nwarren[/quote]\n\nLet me begin by saying that I''ve never even seen these beauties in Pakistan. [b]If[/b] they are available, they''re simply too expensive.\n\nThat said, if given the choice, I''d go for the RWS 48, as I prefer having a side lever over an under-lever. Though I did read good stuff about the Air Arms TX 200, I feel that the 48 is slightly more powerful, and and the extra velocity might be useful at longer ranges, especially with heavier pellets. \n\nUnfortunately, I''ve only heard/ read about the HW97 and the RWS 460 in passing.\n\nAround here, we mostly have break-barrel spring guns, with the Gamo Shadow 1000 being one of the more popular ones.\n\nHere''s a link to our airgun discussion thread:\n[url]http://www.pakguns.com/forum/viewtopic.php?id=1968[/url][/quote]', 0, 1, '71.180.230.128', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2, 58773),
