(51946, 1703, 50102, 'KageFox', 688, '', 1252608307, 'No, regular LEA and military do not use small caliber side-arms, although usage of such weapon is present amongst special forces and intelligence agents. Also, smaller caliber weapons make for better backup guns (.25, .32) due to their (usually) smaller size.\n\nAs Mr Skeeter60 mentioned, the 6.8mm SPC was intended to replace the 5.56mm NATO, however, as of yet, there is no confirmed adoption of the caliber by the U.S. military. According to tests by Future Weapons (Discovery), the 6.8mm SPC fills the energy gap between the 5.56x45mm and the 7.62x39mm. It is particularly suitable for NATO rifles as the length of the cartridge is similar to the 5.56mm.', 0, 1, '110.37.23.208', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 2265, 59036),
